Ghana Gets $167 Million From China for Bui Project, Graphic Says

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-02-17T10:29:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/ghana-gets-167-million-from-china-for-bui-project-graphic-says.html
Ghana  will get an additional $167
million from  China  to help it build its Bui hydroelectric plant,
the Daily Graphic reported, citing the African nation’s Minister
of Finance and  Economic Planning ,  Kwabena Duffuor .  The money is in addition to the $562 million that the
Chinese government has already provided for the project, the
Accra-based newspaper said. China’s Sino Hydro started building
the 400 megawatt hydropower plant in August 2007, the Daily
Graphic said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 